        <briefdescription>
<para>Builds a multisample anti-aliasing (MSAA) framebuffer for high-quality rendering. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>This function creates a framebuffer object (FBO) with multisample support, allowing for smoother edges and reduced aliasing artifacts in rendered images.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>size</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The dimensions (width, height) of the framebuffer in pixels. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>msaa_samples</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The number of MSAA samples to use. Higher values provide better anti-aliasing but may impact performance. Typical values are 2, 4, or 8. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>bits_per_pixel</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The color buffer precision. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>The created <ref refid="structeu_1_1render_1_1FrameBuffer" kindref="compound">FrameBuffer</ref> object with MSAA enabled. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
